matches.notes: Nice game, very few fouls (perhaps four)
Beers for Tears played with only one Lady rest of team Men (10) Therefore they lost by forfeit
Good game. A little bit of chatter from both teams but overall no need for any disciplinary action.

Before the match, Renegades had 8 men and 2  women. The manager for the day, Oscar Garavito, along with Fire N Ice manager Harinder Grewal,  both agreed they would play as-is during our pregame meeting. I checked in additional players for both teams as they arrived to the match. At halftime, Fire N Ice lent some of their players to Renegades and play continued without issues. 

At the end of the match which ended in a 2-0 win for Renegades, I was told by both team managers that Renegades had actually declared a forfeit to Fire N Ice before the match. I said that is something you both need to tell me before the match, because if a team is forfeiting, the ref goes home. In addition, since there were enough players and both teams agreed in my presence to go ahead and play, there should have been no reason to forfeit. I told both managers I would recount our conversations in the ref postgame report and they were in agreement.

Decision to terminate match agreed upon by both managers with official scoring (4-1, favor to Spartans) at 70th minute.  Remaining minutes (up to 90th) were officiated as a friendly with no further scoring officially tracked.
